Hi Bruce .. Are you speaking to the box and responding to &quot;real time&quot; 
answers or do you have to play it back to hear their answers?  Just 
asking because I need to play my recordings back to hear responses ..

Debbie




--- In EVP-ITC@yahoogroups.com, bruce halliday 
&lt;paranormalinvestigating@...&gt; wrote:
&gt;
&gt; 
&gt; Mike,
&gt;  
&gt; I usually start with asking if they will please join me in a 
communication session. If you have a technician and or spirits that 
communicate
&gt; with you on a regular basis, and know their names, greet them and 
thank them for their efforts in communicating and to please send any 
messages
&gt; or respond to any question that you have, and you will do the same. 
Also ask that they block any negative energy or communication or 
spirits themselves 
&gt; from coming through the box. then proceed with the session.
&gt;  
&gt; At the end I ask that any spirits that may have come through the 
open doorway the line of live communication may create, go back 
before the box is turned off.
&gt;  
&gt; wait to here verbal conformation from the other side that it is 
clear to turn the box off. the responses I usually get are Clear, 
Good, Okay or words to that effect.
&gt;  
&gt; I thank my friends for their efforts and say my goodbyes and 
announce that I am turning off the box. I turn it off and the session 
is done.
&gt;  
&gt; Some researchers feel comfortable as I do saying a short protection 
prayer before a session and some do not believe it is necessary. the 
choice is yours.
&gt;  
&gt; I have posted a short protection ritual in the file section of my 
other group, it is there if you need it.
&gt;  
&gt; the link to the group is  
http://tech.groups.yahoo.com/group/EVP_ITC_Researchers/ just go over 
and join.
